    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for western-made, high quality handmade paper with a warm ivory or yellowish color, and a smooth, slightly mottled surface. It was highly valued for printmaking. It is called "japan" because it was thought to resemble Japanese printmaking paper.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
